720217f-b.text:
Greenwich Street, south from Franklin (In No. 1) and Warren (in No's. 2 & 3) Streets, showing the Ninth Avenue elevated line overhanging the Street. Prominent buildings seen in No. 1 are the Woolworth, a loft structure at the S.E. corner of Greenwich and Jay Streets. the new downtown Post Office and the City Bank Farmers Trust Co. Bidg. Views 2 and 3 show mainly the recently completed
Post Office Bldg.
July 4, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3
P. L. Sperr
